Frank doesn&#39;t sell boxes

--- On Thu, 6/12/08, threadsintyme@... &lt;Threadsintyme@...&gt; wrote:

From: threadsintyme@... &lt;Threadsintyme@...&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Frank&#39;s Box and Chris Moon
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Date: Thursday, June 12, 2008, 6:23 PM







Chris Moon really rates well below my theory for humanity! I was invited once to write for his mag. I sent them an email asking how they wanted the copy to be submitted. Either by email or file.
Three years later,&nbsp;I am STILL waiting for the reply to my request!! 
But, I do agree with you however. It is to bad that Frank didn&#39;t have everyone who bought a box to sign a waiver that would prevent the box from being&nbsp;potentially abused by them. 
I wonder, how often is it that Moon actually books a paid session? I know that Moon has been going to different Universities. Most college kids today don&#39;t have that kind of money laying around!&nbsp;
Al

-- &quot;Leah&quot; &lt;leahsodyssey@ yahoo.com&gt; wrote:



I am concerend because Chris Moon is using Frank&#39;s box under his name to make money. He 
charges $250 for a half hour session with this box. I wouldn&#39;t be so irritated had he just 
called it something else, but this is Frank&#39;s and it should be up to Frank how this box is used. 
I think using it to make money is wrong. I am not saying it would be wrong for Frank to 
market it it, at a reasonable price, but to charge $250 for a session that is under the 
interpretation of Chris Moon is just playing on those who are suffering from a loss and 
looking for a connection.



